* We'll begin *

31:17.090 --> 31:19.840
* With a spin *

31:19.890 --> 31:25.350
* Traveling in the world of my creation *

31:25.400 --> 31:27.710
* What we'll see *

31:27.770 --> 31:30.100
* Will defy *

31:30.180 --> 31:36.220
* Explanation *

31:36.270 --> 31:40.780
* If you want to view paradise *

31:40.860 --> 31:45.670
* Simply look around and view it *

31:45.730 --> 31:50.750
* Anything you want to, do it *

31:50.820 --> 31:54.210
* Want to change the world *

31:54.260 --> 31:58.510
* There's nothing to it *

32:01.350 --> 32:05.220
* There is no *

32:05.270 --> 32:08.810
* Life I know *

32:08.890 --> 32:14.310
* To compare with pure imagination *

32:14.400 --> 32:19.620
* Living there, you'll be free *

32:19.700 --> 32:27.120
* If you truly... *

32:29.430 --> 32:39.140
* Wish to be. *.

32:42.260 --> 32:44.090
Thank you.

32:59.110 --> 33:01.310
Sorry.
Long line in the restroom.

33:01.360 --> 33:03.780
Everyone was fixing their mascara.

33:03.830 --> 33:05.660
Mm.

33:05.750 --> 33:07.950
You did such a great job with the funeral.

33:08.000 --> 33:09.500
I'm so proud of you.

33:11.820 --> 33:13.820
Why are you crying?

33:13.890 --> 33:16.120
Because I'm breaking up with you.

33:17.490 --> 33:19.330
Because of Rachel?

33:20.540 --> 33:22.300
'Cause you still love her?

33:22.350 --> 33:24.210
I shouldn't have done this with you.

33:24.300 --> 33:25.880
I thought that I could fix

33:25.950 --> 33:28.940
everything from last year, but I...

33:29.000 --> 33:30.970
I can't.

33:31.040 --> 33:33.020
I just can't, and

33:33.110 --> 33:36.530
that feeling that Sue was
talking about in there of being

33:36.610 --> 33:39.850
tethered to someone...
I... I just...

33:39.900 --> 33:42.200
I don't feel that way about you.

33:42.280 --> 33:44.180
But you do with her?

33:46.040 --> 33:47.950
No.

33:48.020 --> 33:49.740
We're not breaking up.

33:49.820 --> 33:51.630
I can handle your confusion with Rachel

33:51.690 --> 33:53.240
until you get over it.

33:53.330 --> 33:54.580
We're gonna stay together,

33:54.660 --> 33:56.860
and next year,
we'll be prom king and queen...

33:56.910 --> 33:57.910
Just stop it.

33:59.030 --> 34:00.530
Okay? I don't want that life.

34:02.500 --> 34:04.700
Don't you feel anything anymore?

34:04.770 --> 34:06.690
This is real.

34:06.760 --> 34:08.060
This is happening.

34:14.270 --> 34:16.179
Are you happy now?

34:18.070 --> 34:19.739
Is this me feeling enough for you?

34:19.820 --> 34:21.889
Quinn, I'm sorry.
I still love you.

34:21.940 --> 34:23.020
Just don't touch me!

34:41.610 --> 34:42.780
Action.

34:43.100 --> 34:44.380
Well, it was a tough competition,

34:44.429 --> 34:45.110
but here's the dope.

34:45.150 --> 34:47.780
Santana... too mean.
Kurt... too controversial.

34:47.800 --> 34:50.110
Mercedes... I said it twice,
and I'll say it again.

34:50.130 --> 34:52.610
Lazy B-O-N-E-S.

34:52.670 --> 34:54.000
Rachel is the clear winner.

34:54.030 --> 34:56.530
I'm really not comfortable
having this conversation taped.

34:56.600 --> 34:59.120
Well, I can't practice reality
show judging without a camera.

34:59.200 --> 35:00.700
It's like practicing skiing without skis.

35:00.770 --> 35:02.070
I've totally done that.

35:02.120 --> 35:04.040
Okay, Brittany, can you
just turn that thing off?

35:04.110 --> 35:06.240
Just the off switch... right...
right over there. Just...

35:06.290 --> 35:07.440
Yeah, I know how
to turn it off. Thanks.

35:07.500 --> 35:09.710
Okay. It's cool.

35:09.780 --> 35:11.620
Jessie, maybe you can come on.

35:11.670 --> 35:13.080
<i>Fondue for Two</i> and judge my Cat.

35:13.150 --> 35:16.000
Rock and roll.
I have to be honest, Jessie.

35:16.090 --> 35:17.390
The more we talk about this,

35:17.460 --> 35:18.640
the more uncomfortable
I feel about all of it.

35:18.720 --> 35:20.060
It just feels like I'm telling

35:20.120 --> 35:21.640
one of my children
that they're my favorite.

35:21.730 --> 35:23.580
Well, that's what my parents
told me in front of my siblings.

35:23.650 --> 35:24.610
Sure, some might say that it led

35:24.680 --> 35:26.430
to my brother's whippet addiction

35:26.500 --> 35:29.130
and my sister's bulimia, but
my parents owed them the truth.

35:31.140 --> 35:34.270
You really think picking Rachel
means we beat Vocal Adrenaline?

35:34.320 --> 35:35.840
It's in the bag.

35:39.480 --> 35:41.610
Coach, can I come in?

35:41.660 --> 35:43.860
Hello, Becky.

35:43.950 --> 35:48.290
I'm turning in my pom-poms
and the megaphone

35:48.340 --> 35:49.820
that you got me.

35:49.870 --> 35:52.340
I'll miss our time together...

35:52.420 --> 35:54.660
I'm gonna stop you right there, Becky.

35:54.710 --> 35:57.260
Have you ever heard of menopause?

35:57.330 --> 36:00.100
Well, I fired you in a hormonal fury

36:00.160 --> 36:03.680
I like to call womb rage, and I apologize.

36:03.770 --> 36:06.100
Now I'd like you to
pick up those pom-poms

36:06.170 --> 36:07.350
and that megaphone.

36:07.440 --> 36:08.940
You know why?

36:09.010 --> 36:11.480
Next year, you're Captain of the Cheerios!

36:11.530 --> 36:13.390
Oh, my gosh, thanks, Coach!

36:14.360 --> 36:15.610
Got to call my mom!

36:15.680 --> 36:17.530
Uh, hold it right there.

36:17.620 --> 36:19.530
I'm not finished.

36:19.620 --> 36:21.150
I want you to give me a hug.

36:22.900 --> 36:24.740
Come here.

36:38.000 --> 36:40.140
That seat taken?

36:40.200 --> 36:42.040
No.

36:46.260 --> 36:48.810
William, I have to say something.

36:48.880 --> 36:50.180
In the history of our relationship,

36:50.250 --> 36:52.830
I've said many things to you,

36:52.900 --> 36:54.970
but there's one thing I've never said.

36:55.040 --> 36:57.220
Good luck.

36:57.290 --> 36:59.320
You know, I spent all this time hating you,

36:59.390 --> 37:00.660
and hating that Glee Club.

37:00.730 --> 37:02.880
I do this thing where I sort of alternate

37:02.940 --> 37:04.860
which one of those kids I hate the most.

37:04.930 --> 37:06.580
Right now, it's the dancing Asian.

37:06.660 --> 37:08.550
But after what you did for my sister,

37:08.620 --> 37:11.840
I just can't do it anymore.

37:11.900 --> 37:15.540
You have something Jean
had that I do not have.

37:17.010 --> 37:19.180
A pure heart.

37:19.240 --> 37:20.710
You're a very good friend, William,

37:20.780 --> 37:22.910
and I have not been that to you.

37:22.980 --> 37:24.130
Yeah, you really haven't.

37:24.200 --> 37:25.850
So, it's time for a change.

37:25.920 --> 37:28.420
Starting today, I will no longer
be going after the Glee Club.

37:28.470 --> 37:31.100
Frankly, I have bigger fish to fry.

37:31.190 --> 37:33.560
I'm running for the United
States House of Representatives.

37:35.780 --> 37:37.110
I'm... I'm sorry.

37:37.200 --> 37:38.460
What-What did you say?

37:38.530 --> 37:40.360
In the last year of her life,

37:40.430 --> 37:42.480
Jean faced ballooning health care costs

37:42.550 --> 37:45.600
and cuts to her disability payments.

37:45.650 --> 37:48.240
Well, the Sue Sylvester
American Liberty Party thinks

37:48.290 --> 37:50.840
that's a load of phooey.

37:50.910 --> 37:52.660
There is one slight problem.

37:52.740 --> 37:56.410
In a fit of pique, I rerouted
the Glee Club's plane to Libya.

37:56.480 --> 37:57.660
Wait... what?!

37:57.730 --> 37:58.830
It took some effort.

37:58.920 --> 38:00.800
It was a long fit of pique.

38:00.870 --> 38:03.340
I had some help... Panda Express
really came through for me.

38:03.420 --> 38:04.860
So we're not going to New York?

38:04.920 --> 38:06.590
I can explain that.

38:09.480 --> 38:10.890
Will, I'm gonna leave you two alone,

38:10.960 --> 38:12.480
as this just became super awkward.

38:14.020 --> 38:15.850
These are first-class tickets
on American Airlines.

38:15.930 --> 38:17.270
How did you afford them?

38:17.320 --> 38:19.150
Well, do you know that if you complain

38:19.240 --> 38:20.850
to the airline about contracting monkey pox

38:20.940 --> 38:22.520
in the bathroom on the plane,

38:22.610 --> 38:24.440
you can get the president of the airline

38:24.490 --> 38:25.910
on the phone within an hour?

38:25.980 --> 38:27.490
But you didn't?
No, of course not.

38:27.580 --> 38:29.360
Have you been on their planes?
They're immaculate.

38:29.450 --> 38:31.750
No, it turns out that one
of the vice presidents

38:31.820 --> 38:33.320
of American Airlines is a big supporter

38:33.370 --> 38:34.530
of the arts or something,

38:34.620 --> 38:36.870
so when I told him
your Glee Club's sob story,

38:36.950 --> 38:38.510
he gladly came up with the tickets

38:38.590 --> 38:40.040
for you guys to make it happen.

38:40.120 --> 38:42.710
This is amazing, Terri.

38:42.790 --> 38:44.710
Wait.

38:44.800 --> 38:46.680
What's the catch?

38:46.760 --> 38:48.430
I'm moving to Miami.

38:48.500 --> 38:50.830
Sheets N' Things is opening
a new branch down there,

38:50.890 --> 38:52.470
and they have asked me to manage it.

38:52.520 --> 38:54.220
Like, full on manager?

38:54.310 --> 38:57.520
The assistant title is officially dropped.

38:57.610 --> 38:59.840
Look, Will, I know that I made your life...

38:59.890 --> 39:03.230
Challenging sometimes, but...

39:05.480 --> 39:07.780
...it was only because
I loved you so much.

39:07.850 --> 39:09.990
I loved you, too.

39:10.040 --> 39:12.020
We just weren't right.

39:13.490 --> 39:14.460
No regrets, though.

39:14.530 --> 39:16.540
No. Not one.

39:22.220 --> 39:24.250
Just try to relax a little bit while

39:24.340 --> 39:25.640
you're down there, okay?

39:25.700 --> 39:26.890
Oh. Yeah.
I mean, you deserve

39:26.970 --> 39:27.670
to enjoy yourself.

39:27.720 --> 39:29.260
Okay.

39:29.340 --> 39:31.210
Okay.

39:33.340 --> 39:35.380
I'll see you around, Will.

39:40.350 --> 39:41.570
Hey.
Hey.

39:41.650 --> 39:43.550
Is everything okay with Terri?

39:43.600 --> 39:45.110
Yeah. Finally.

39:45.190 --> 39:46.690
It is.

39:46.740 --> 39:49.060
Is... Are you wearing
one of my old vests?

39:49.110 --> 39:51.610
Yeah, I didn't have the
heart to throw it away.

39:53.080 --> 39:54.280
Emma, this isn't forever.

39:54.370 --> 39:57.120
I hope it is.

39:57.190 --> 39:59.750
Really, Will, you deserve this.

39:59.840 --> 40:03.160
You've given so much for so long,

40:03.220 --> 40:05.290
and now it's your turn.

40:05.380 --> 40:07.880
But, um, don't be a stranger, okay?

40:12.380 --> 40:14.130
Thank you.

40:27.930 --> 40:28.900
Jessie?

40:28.950 --> 40:30.270
That's sweet.

40:30.320 --> 40:32.100
You remember the masculine
click of my designer boots.

40:32.150 --> 40:33.450
Okay, why did you ask me

40:33.540 --> 40:34.790
to meet you here right
before the list goes up?

40:34.870 --> 40:36.070
Is this good news, or is it bad news?

40:36.120 --> 40:38.210
Rachel, I did wrong by you last year,

40:38.280 --> 40:40.580
and I came back to make that wrong right.

40:40.630 --> 40:42.380
And I came here to tell you

40:42.450 --> 40:44.820
that you're going
to be the featured soloist

40:44.880 --> 40:46.220
at Nationals in New York.

40:46.280 --> 40:47.550
Wait, wait. How do you know?

40:47.620 --> 40:48.720
Did Mr. Schuester tell you?

40:48.790 --> 40:49.970
Let it suffice to say

40:50.050 --> 40:51.620
that I was very involved in the decision.

40:53.890 --> 40:55.460
Oh.

40:58.510 --> 41:00.350
No. I-I... I feel bad.

41:00.430 --> 41:01.970
Everyone else worked so hard.

41:02.020 --> 41:03.850
Now they're just going to hate me.

41:03.940 --> 41:05.820
They sort of already do, and

41:05.900 --> 41:07.350
you know as well as I

41:07.440 --> 41:09.570
that sometimes that's the price of fame.

41:11.750 --> 41:15.370
I used to think that fame was
the only thing that mattered.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.250
And now I realize that there's something

41:17.310 --> 41:18.770
that matters to me more.

41:18.860 --> 41:20.930
What?

41:20.990 --> 41:22.480
You.

41:30.030 --> 41:31.380
Come on.

41:31.620 --> 41:33.570
I think the list is posted.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.380
This doesn't make any sense.

41:43.470 --> 41:44.970
Guys, it was a tough decision,

41:45.040 --> 41:46.300
but it's for the good of the club.

41:46.370 --> 41:47.470
Although this is deeply personal,

41:47.540 --> 41:48.870
try not to take it personally.

41:48.920 --> 41:51.890
Um, you guys might want
to read what the list says.

41:51.980 --> 41:53.310
What? Why?

41:58.770 --> 42:01.150
Oh, Mr. Shue,
thank God you're here

42:01.220 --> 42:02.820
to put these trolls out of their
misery. Can you just announce

42:02.890 --> 42:04.520
my win so that I can get on
with teasing the losers?

42:04.570 --> 42:05.720
I heard your performance, Santana.

42:05.770 --> 42:07.240
This is mine, and you know it.

42:07.320 --> 42:08.890
See, Jessie? This is
the kind of infighting

42:08.940 --> 42:10.830
and "me first" attitudes
that I wanted to avoid.

42:10.890 --> 42:12.660
What you call infighting,
I call motivation.

42:12.730 --> 42:14.500
And this is just the beginning.
Once we get to Nationals,

42:14.560 --> 42:16.620
I'll have them willing to kill
each other for that solo.

42:16.700 --> 42:19.170
No.

42:19.240 --> 42:20.870
I've changed my mind.

42:20.920 --> 42:23.340
We're going back to what got us here...

42:23.410 --> 42:25.570
Original songs sung by the entire club.

42:25.630 --> 42:27.630
We're a team,

42:27.710 --> 42:29.630
and we're best when we work as one.

42:29.710 --> 42:30.550
You're going to lose.

42:30.600 --> 42:32.350
Whatever we do,

42:32.420 --> 42:34.520
we're going to do it together.

42:34.580 --> 42:37.750
Actually, Santana, you sounded pretty good.

42:37.810 --> 42:40.140
Thanks. You guys were all
pretty dope, too.

42:40.220 --> 42:41.720
Even Rachel.

42:41.780 --> 42:43.430
I wish I could sound like you do, Santana.

42:43.480 --> 42:44.810
I mean, how do you get that raspiness?

42:44.900 --> 42:47.110
So nice. I smoke cigars.

42:47.180 --> 42:48.780
All right, guys, time to get to work.

42:48.870 --> 42:50.200
Now, I want two hit songs

42:50.270 --> 42:52.450
by the time the wheels
touch down at JFK. Come on.

42:55.910 --> 42:59.960
Hey. Thanks.
For what?

43:00.040 --> 43:01.880
I know you're hurting right now,

43:01.950 --> 43:04.880
but it's really cool
you didn't quit Glee Club.

43:04.950 --> 43:06.350
If I quit Glee Club, my big plans

43:06.420 --> 43:07.470
for New York would have been ruined.

43:07.530 --> 43:09.120
What plans?
You'll see.

